    New monsters pack

    Description

    New Monsters Pack
    Explore the expanded horizons of the New Monsters Pack, an addition to Heroes of Might and Magic III that enriches gameplay with powerful new creatures, abilities, and heroes.
    An Array of Powerful Units
    Unleash a lineup of formidable units, including the corrosive Acidic Roper, the stealthy Dragonfish, and the mighty Forest Dragon and T-Rex. Each creature brings unique skills and enhances the strategic depth of battles.
    New Heroes and Enhanced Abilities
    Meet the latest heroes to join the ranks, such as Cintia, a master of interference, Marlon, who enhances sorcery, and Boudicca, known for preventing enemy retreats. These heroes, with their special abilities, provide new strategic options for the battlefield.
    Unique Spells and Skills
    Harness the powers of spells like Magic Carpet for tactical mobility, Red Paralysis to immobilize foes, and Fame, which boosts creature growth rates. These additions empower players with new ways to dominate the battlefield.
    Created to expand and deepen the Heroes of Might and Magic III experience, the New Monsters Pack offers rich content for strategists and adventurers alike. Embark on quests with these new units and spells, and conquer the battlefield in style.

    1.2.6

    Heroes

    Name Biography Gender Image Specialty
    Ama'Ka She has a great talent for finding an oases in the desert. She once even accidentally found a desert geyser called the Holy Source of Life. Nowadays she often goes there with her army, which makes her troops more vital than other troops found in the desert. female Aura of Life
    Ankh-Amon In cities of wizards, there is little room for women, especially for women like Ankh-Amon, for whom expanding knowledge is less important than enhancing magical talent. After years of wandering, she found her place among the viziers in the Bracada desert. female Sorcery
    Basha Basha loves trinkets, in particular affection has for crystals. She can find even the smallest crystal hidden in desert sands, which makes her one of the most respected nobles of the desert. female Crystals
    Mentuhotep Deserts always hide treasures, as Mentuhotep firmly believes. He is proven right whenever he discoveres great riches there. Subsequently, he settled in one of the desert cities, where he expanded his wealth. male +350 Gold
    Kemi Kemi hails from Tatalia. She was an apprentice blacksmith who learned everything from her master before moving south. The swampy areas never suited her, so she settled within the protective walls of Shazad, where she served as a blacksmith for the army. After becoming very popular, she overthrew a local pharaoh and took his place on the throne. female Armorer
    Inpu Pharaoh Inpu is a legendary ruler known for his extraordinary magical abilities. Through mysterious rituals, he can transform sphinxes of various subspecies, including living and undead sphinxes, lamias, manticores, and scorpicores, into powerful guardian sphinxes. His reign is a time of great protection and stability, as the guardian sphinxes guard the borders of his kingdom against all threats. male Master of Sphinxes
    Isham As everyone knows, Sekhmets do not like to hurry, they do everything gracefully and calmly. But Isham is different, when riding her horse she can overtake other riders with the speed of a sandstorm. female Logistics
    Ta-Kem Ta-Kem spent her whole life studying various scrolls about geology. When times have changed and he was sent to war, she learned to use the acquired knowledge in practice, so she can always find firmer ground to move quickly. female Pathfinding
    Bianor Anubians are known for their magical nature, but Bianor have always been fascinated with engineering. He brought a few ballistas to his palace basement, where he got them upgraded. During battles his war mashines can kill up to 20 people with a single shot. male Ballista
    Honsuneb Pharaoh Honsuneb is a legendary ruler who can command powerful desert winged serpents. His ability to control these mythical creatures brings him great strength and respect among his subjects. With his power, Honsuneb maintains order and security in his kingdom. male Wadjets
    Ja'Bak The Supreme Pharaoh, the greatest lord of the Bracada desert, charismatic Anubis hungry for power. During his reign, the great Golden City became the largest trade center in the south Antagarich. male Anubis Warriors
    Uzziah Uzziah, the right-handed knopesh master, found his best camel alone in the depths of the dunes. It soon turned out, that it is the fastest camel known to everyone across the desert, so Uzziah named him Me'nzzen, which means 'Leader of the party'. He didn't have to wait a long time until many other camel riders came to him to ride under his banner. Now, together they roam the desert spreading terror among the enemies of the Grand Pharaoh. male Camel Riders
    Netsutset They say that it was Netsutset who brought the ammuts to the cities. The first ammuts were summoned from some kind of terrifying realm via a dark ritual ordered by Netsutset and performed by crocodile priests. Despite their wild nature, he managed to tame and train these otherworldly beings. male Ammuts
    Keknutt Some Sekhmets do not believe in their own resurrection, but legends do not lie. Keknutt is a good example; she died and rose from the dead with a new appearance. Now, instead of being half lion and half human, she looks like a humanoid frog. She tells her sister that she believed in the resurrection and was not afraid of death. Inspired by her story and transformation, all Sekhmets now go into battle without fear, confident in the promise of resurrection and emboldened by Keknutt's miraculous return. female Sekhmets
    Mex-Nefer Mex-Nefer began to serve in the temple of the Four Winds since childhood. Through years she was known both for her great wisdom and also cruelty. For her cruelty was banished from the city. But after spending a long time in the desert, she learned to predict the behavior of the wind, and use it for their own purposes and recall at the appropriate time. female Haste
    Mantis He hails from Bracada and graduated from the prestigious Academy of Mages, where he specialized in the intricate and ancient desert aspects of earth magic. Driven by an insatiable thirst for knowledge and power, he left his hometown after a few years to seek out more potent and elusive forms of magic. The mystical allure of the desert cities captivated him, and he chose to settle there. Immersed in the enigmatic and harsh landscapes, he honed his magical abilities to new heights, delving deep into the secrets of the sands and the earth. His journey through the deserts not only enhanced his powers but also transformed him into a mage of formidable skill and wisdom. male Quicksand Master
    Amshah Amshah was one of the flagellants freed from captivity by Ja'Bak. After his liberation, he decided to stay in Tilafa, where he found a new life and mission. Today, he is responsible for other escapees from cities occupied by knights, providing them with shelter and assistance in adapting to their new reality. With his experience and knowledge, he has become a mentor and leader, helping former prisoners find their way in freedom and build new, stable lives in Tilafa. His courage and determination are an inspiration to many who have endured similar traumas. male Whippers
